Jay Marchant https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Jay_Marchant 0 Jay Marchant (January 7, 1888 – June 14, 1962) was an American film director and actor of the silent era. He directed 22 films between 1921 and 1925, including five film serials for the Universal Film Manufacturing Company. He was born in Tripp County, South Dakota and died in Los Angeles County, California. Jay_Marchant ( January_7_,_1888 – June_14_,_1962 ) was an_American_film_director_and_actor of the_silent_era .
